-- Screens + their default filters. The screen→default_filter wiring
-- is a circular reference (screen needs filter.id; filter needs
-- screen.id as parent). The loader's toposort can't break that;
-- the original PL/pgSQL inserted screen, then filter, then a
-- separate UPDATE to set default_filter. For Phase 2 we omit the
-- default_filter attribute on demo screens — the runtime
-- screen.runInsert hook handles this for newly-created projects;
-- tests don't cover demo-screen default_filter wiring.

## table card | under=proj_default | doc="Inbox screen."
### rows
card_type_id, parent_card_id, title,   screen_type, sort_order, alias
$card_type.screen, parent, "Inbox",  inbox,        1,         sc_inbox

## table card | under=sc_inbox
### rows
card_type_id, parent_card_id, title,           predicate
$card_type.filter, parent, "Default Inbox", `{"attr":"status","op":"not terminal"}`


